# KPI Definitions

## Business Goal #1: User Adoption

**Metric:** Monthly Active Users (MAU)
- **Definition:** Unique users who used product in past 30 days
- **Target:** 20,000 by end of Q2
- **Current:** 12,450
- **Owner:** Growth team

**Leading Indicators:**
- DAU (Daily Active Users) - early signal of engagement
- Signup rate - top of funnel health
- Email open rate - user interest

**Lagging Indicators:**
- Churn rate - ultimate health metric
- NPS - user satisfaction

---

## Business Goal #2: AI Quality

**Metric:** Output Accuracy
- **Definition:** % of AI responses rated 4-5 on 5-point quality scale
- **Target:** 85%
- **Current:** 78%
- **Owner:** AI/Product team

**Leading Indicators:**
- Prompt variant test results
- User feedback sentiment
- Support tickets about "wrong answer"

**Lagging Indicators:**
- Retention for power users
- Premium tier adoption

---

## Business Goal #3: Revenue

**Metric:** Monthly Recurring Revenue (MRR)
- **Definition:** Revenue from active subscriptions
- **Target:** $50K by Q3
- **Current:** $28,500
- **Owner:** Monetization team

**Leading Indicators:**
- Trial signup rate
- Trial-to-paid conversion
- Premium tier adoption rate

**Lagging Indicators:**
- Customer lifetime value
- Expansion revenue per customer
